pomodoro4linux is a way to get the most out of time management. Turn time into a valuable ally to accomplish
what we want to do and chart continuous improvement in the way we do it, in other words, a tool to manage
your time better.

The basic steps of pomodoro4linux:
    1. Choose a task to be accomplished.
    2. Run pomodoro4linux. (See more in How-to).
    3. Work on this task until the pomodoro4linux show you a short notice.
    4. Take a break for 5 minutes.
    5. Every 4 rounds of pomodoro4linux, take a longer break.

How-to
    Run the script pomodoro.py, like:
        python ~/pomodoro4linux/pomodoro/pomodoro.py
